snippet: A Florida jury heard conflicting stories about the shooting of a teenager during an argument over loud music in 2012.
abstract: Michael Dunn, Florida man accused of fatally shooting 17-year-old black student Jordan Davis, tells Jacksonville jury that his decision to fire repeatedly at vehicle in gas station was matter of self-defense; Dunn struggles to preserve his credibility after his distraught fiancee takes stand and contradicted some major points of his testimony.
lead_paragraph: A Florida jury heard conflicting stories about the shooting of a teenager during an argument over loud music in 2012.

headline.main: Florida Man’s Fiancée Contradicts Parts of His Testimony in Killing of Teenager
headline.print_headline: Florida Man’s Fiancée Contradicts Parts of His Testimony in Killing of Teenager
